            "class_1_1_3": {
              "title": "DevOps vs Traditional IT",
              "description": "Key differences and benefits",
              "content_type": "text",
              "duration": 300,
              "order": 3,
              "text_content": "## DevOps vs Traditional IT\n\nDevOps represents a fundamental shift in how software is developed and deployed.\n\n### Traditional IT:\n- **Siloed teams**: Development and Operations work separately\n- **Manual processes**: Deployments done manually\n- **Long release cycles**: Months between releases\n- **Reactive**: Issues addressed after they occur\n\n### DevOps:\n- **Collaborative culture**: Dev and Ops work together\n- **Automation**: CI/CD pipelines automate deployments\n- **Continuous delivery**: Multiple deployments per day\n- **Proactive**: Monitoring and prevention\n\n### Key Benefits:\n1. **Faster time to market**\n2. **Higher quality software**\n3. **Better collaboration**\n4. **Improved customer satisfaction**\n5. **Reduced costs**"
            }
